The article is a briefing by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and UN Ambassador Susan Rice. They discuss President Obama's upcoming visit to the United Nations General Assembly and the work the US has been doing at the UN to advance its interests and make Americans safer. They mention the global challenges the US faces, such as nuclear threats, terrorism, climate change, and international criminal networks, and emphasize the importance of international cooperation in dealing with these challenges. They also mention the principles that guide the US's approach to the UN, including promoting national security interests, participating constructively, and standing firm on important issues.